        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/javierlorente.es">@javierlorente.es</a>,</p>
<p>For any WordPress plugin you want to use in your Frontity project you have to take into account the following</p>
<h3>If you just want to display data provided by the plugin</h3>
<p>Then you have to make sure this data is shared via REST API. From there, Frontity will be able to access this data an make it available to your React components</p>
<h3>If you need to interact with the plugin</h3>
<p>If you need to interact with the plugin somehow (sending data for example), then the recommended approach is to create a <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/learning-frontity/packages">Frontity package</a> that encapsulates the logic required to communicate with that plugin</p>
<p>Here you have some examples of packages created to communicate with specific plugins</p>
